In a four-day-old chick of the American black swift, a temperature drop of 15 Â° C was observed in 28 minutes. By the time the chicks are able to independently regulate the temperature, they reach 75% of the mass of an adult bird. size on the 32-33rd day, primary flight feathers, starting with the outer feather, on the 13th day. Tail feathers appear at the age of 12-14 days, feathers on the head - 18-21 days. Birds fly out of the nest when the eighth the primary feather reaches its adult size, in the tenth - 90% of the size of the feather of an adult bird, the tail plumage reaches the same size.